1
00:00:04,416 --> 00:00:06,583
[footsteps shuffling]

2
00:00:10,458 --> 00:00:12,916
Watari: Aw, man.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,000
So much for that, huh?

4
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:17,916
Win Nationals this time around,

5
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:20,666
sweep all three years
of high school,

6
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:24,416
throw Japan into Watari fever,

7
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:26,500
move to the U.K. reluctantly,

8
00:00:26,583 --> 00:00:29,458
get into trouble
with a bunch of supermodels,

9
00:00:29,541 --> 00:00:30,875
lead the league in goals,

10
00:00:30,958 --> 00:00:32,333
win ten<i> Ballon d'Or</i> in a row.

11
00:00:32,416 --> 00:00:34,583
[cat meows]

12
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:36,500
I had the whole thing
mapped out, you know.

13
00:00:36,583 --> 00:00:40,250
Us losing this year
wasn't part of the plan.

14
00:00:44,125 --> 00:00:46,291
So much for becoming
a soccer star.

15
00:00:50,166 --> 00:00:52,458
- What's the road to fame
without a couple setbacks?

16
00:00:52,541 --> 00:00:55,291
Messi had some.

17
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:56,333
Better story that way.

18
00:00:56,416 --> 00:01:00,458
- If so, then I think
you got us all beat.

19
00:01:00,541 --> 00:01:01,041
[chuckles]

20
00:01:02,916 --> 00:01:04,125
I'm handing off the whole

21
00:01:04,208 --> 00:01:07,208
"win big this year" baton
to you, Kousei.

22
00:01:07,291 --> 00:01:08,625
- What if I'm not
a win-big kind of guy?

23
00:01:08,708 --> 00:01:11,458
- Nothing wrong with that.

24
00:01:11,541 --> 00:01:12,416
We've all got strengths.

25
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,625
Mine is soccer.

26
00:01:14,708 --> 00:01:17,416
Tsubaki's is being
really bossy, I guess.

27
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:19,041
Yours is piano.

28
00:01:20,625 --> 00:01:22,041
Still can't hear it?

29
00:01:26,916 --> 00:01:28,333
[young]<i> I'm scared.</i>

30
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,083
I can't get it out of my head.

31
00:01:33,125 --> 00:01:33,583
<i>I'm scared.</i>

32
00:01:33,666 --> 00:01:36,833
<i>I'm scared.</i>

33
00:01:36,916 --> 00:01:38,708
What if...

34
00:01:40,375 --> 00:01:44,166
What if I go out there
and the notes are just gone?

35
00:01:44,250 --> 00:01:45,500
- [chuckles]

36
00:01:45,583 --> 00:01:49,333
What's the road to fame without
a couple setbacks, right?

37
00:01:50,583 --> 00:01:52,208
Facing adversity,

38
00:01:52,291 --> 00:01:55,000
that's how you find out
if you're the real deal.

39
00:01:55,083 --> 00:01:56,916
See the stars?

40
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:57,125
[chuckles]

41
00:02:01,583 --> 00:02:04,166
They're always out,

42
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:06,250
but they shine
the brightest at night.

43
00:02:08,791 --> 00:02:11,750
["Hikaru Nara" playing]

44
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:18,083
♪♪

45
00:02:18,166 --> 00:02:24,375
♪♪

46
00:02:24,458 --> 00:02:26,333
[singing in Japanese]

47
00:02:26,416 --> 00:02:35,458
♪♪

48
00:02:35,541 --> 00:02:44,833
♪♪

49
00:02:44,916 --> 00:02:54,208
♪♪

50
00:02:54,291 --> 00:03:02,583
♪♪

51
00:03:02,666 --> 00:03:12,708
♪♪

52
00:03:12,791 --> 00:03:22,083
♪♪

53
00:03:22,166 --> 00:03:31,458
♪♪

54
00:03:31,541 --> 00:03:40,708
♪♪

55
00:03:40,791 --> 00:03:42,708
[playing
"Etude Opus 25, Number 5"]

56
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:53,458
- That's Chopin's
"Etude Opus 25, Number 5"?

57
00:03:53,541 --> 00:03:55,583
- Why is he speeding through it?

58
00:03:55,666 --> 00:03:57,916
- It's sounding really rough.

59
00:04:01,333 --> 00:04:02,875
<i>- He's playing like he did</i>
<i>at Kaori's competition.</i>

60
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:05,791
<i>The notes are everywhere.</i>

61
00:04:06,625 --> 00:04:08,833
<i>And he's only getting faster.</i>

62
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,583
[water flowing]

63
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:13,875
- [distorted music playing]
- [keys thumping]

64
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:15,166
Kousei:<i> This again.</i>

65
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:19,166
[pedal thumping]

66
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:24,875
<i>It's not ringing out.</i>

67
00:04:26,125 --> 00:04:27,625
<i>I've lost it.</i>

68
00:04:28,833 --> 00:04:31,625
<i>There's nothing.</i>

69
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:33,375
<i>The ocean's rising up</i>
<i>to swallow me.</i>

70
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:38,166
[drop echoes]

71
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:40,625
["Etude Opus 25, Number 5"
continues]

72
00:04:40,708 --> 00:04:41,333
<i>Not yet.</i>

73
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:43,166
<i>Focus. Focus, damn it.</i>

74
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:43,375
<i>Come on.</i>

75
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:47,916
<i>Nothing exists right now</i>
<i>but this piano.</i>

76
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,958
<i>Cling to every note.</i>

77
00:04:52,333 --> 00:04:54,500
<i>Hold on to them all</i>
<i>for dear life!</i>

78
00:05:00,333 --> 00:05:02,041
-<i> You brought this</i>
<i>upon yourself, Kousei.</i>

79
00:05:02,125 --> 00:05:03,291
- [gasps]

80
00:05:04,750 --> 00:05:06,625
-<i> It's punishment</i>

81
00:05:06,708 --> 00:05:09,166
<i>for rejecting my dream,</i>

82
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:11,291
<i>for rejecting me.</i>

83
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:15,791
<i>But you're well aware</i>
<i>of that, aren't you?</i>

84
00:05:17,208 --> 00:05:19,583
<i>You threw it all away.</i>

85
00:05:19,666 --> 00:05:20,750
[blows]

86
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:24,375
[blow echoes]

87
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:26,000
[silence]

88
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:27,875
["Etude Opus 25, Number 5"
continues]

89
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:29,458
-<i> He's atrocious.</i>

90
00:05:29,541 --> 00:05:33,041
<i>- So it's true.</i>
<i>He can't hear it.</i>

91
00:05:33,125 --> 00:05:35,916
<i>- How long does he</i>
<i>mean to torture us?</i>

92
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,083
-<i> What happened?</i>

93
00:05:37,166 --> 00:05:39,708
<i>He played the opening perfectly</i>

94
00:05:39,791 --> 00:05:40,791
<i>and not a single note</i>
<i>out of place,</i>

95
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:42,416
<i>and now this.</i>

96
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,833
<i>The rumors, are they true?</i>

97
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:51,833
<i>What you're giving us is</i>
<i>the sound of a soul in agony.</i>

98
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:56,041
Kousei:<i> Even with</i>
<i>the notes locked away,</i>

99
00:05:56,125 --> 00:05:57,916
<i>I know that it sounds wrong.</i>

100
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,916
<i>I'm butchering Chopin.</i>

101
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,000
<i>- You brought this</i>
<i>upon yourself.</i>

102
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:04,083
-<i> You're wrong.</i>

103
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:06,750
-<i> The notes are gone, Kousei.</i>

104
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:07,916
-<i> You're wrong!</i>

105
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,583
<i>I tried.</i>

106
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:13,000
<i>I tried my very best</i>
<i>out there for you, Mom!</i>

107
00:06:13,833 --> 00:06:17,083
-<i> The piano is a part of you.</i>

108
00:06:17,166 --> 00:06:19,125
<i>But it won't obey you now,</i>
<i>will it,</i>

109
00:06:19,208 --> 00:06:22,833
<i>no matter how hard you try?</i>

110
00:06:23,916 --> 00:06:25,041
<i>You know the reason,</i>

111
00:06:25,125 --> 00:06:27,875
<i>the reason you're alone.</i>

112
00:06:27,958 --> 00:06:30,958
-<i> Now I just wish you were dead!</i>

113
00:06:32,375 --> 00:06:34,166
Saki:<i> This is your fault.</i>

114
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,458
["Etude Opus 25, Number 5"
continues]

115
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,666
-<i> What if I stop?</i>

116
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:48,208
- [gasps]

117
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,083
<i>I can hear the ice in him</i>
<i>starting to thaw.</i>

118
00:06:52,166 --> 00:06:55,208
<i>Is he about to quit?</i>

119
00:06:56,416 --> 00:06:58,833
-<i> What did I expect of myself?</i>

120
00:06:58,916 --> 00:07:00,041
<i>Play like I did with her?</i>

121
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:01,625
<i>Recapture that magic?</i>

122
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,000
<i>I was sure this competition</i>

123
00:07:06,083 --> 00:07:08,041
<i>would spark a change in me,</i>

124
00:07:08,125 --> 00:07:11,750
<i>but I-I'm still frozen there,</i>

125
00:07:11,833 --> 00:07:13,083
<i>trapped in her shadow.</i>

126
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:13,791
-<i> No.</i>

127
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,041
<i>Don't stop.</i>

128
00:07:16,125 --> 00:07:17,708
- Look at him.

129
00:07:17,791 --> 00:07:20,166
- Why does it feel
like he's gonna give up?

130
00:07:20,250 --> 00:07:21,333
- Arima's done it before.
- [audience murmuring]

131
00:07:21,416 --> 00:07:24,791
- He's only going
to dig himself deeper.

132
00:07:24,875 --> 00:07:26,833
-<i> Keep playing. Don't stop.</i>

133
00:07:26,916 --> 00:07:28,208
-<i> Please don't choke.</i>

134
00:07:28,291 --> 00:07:33,666
♪♪

135
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:38,083
♪♪

136
00:07:38,166 --> 00:07:39,458
Kaori:<i> Look at this.</i>

137
00:07:39,541 --> 00:07:43,208
<i>Yeah, check out</i>
<i>your entry number.</i>

138
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:46,208
<i>As in Kochel number 265,</i>

139
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:49,250
<i>as in Mozart's "Twinkle,</i>
<i>Twinkle, Little Star."</i>

140
00:07:51,833 --> 00:07:54,458
<i>It means that you're gonna</i>
<i>shine like a star up there.</i>

141
00:07:57,291 --> 00:08:01,375
-<i> No way. Is this a joke?</i>

142
00:08:01,458 --> 00:08:03,958
<i>That can't be the Arima I know.</i>

143
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:07,041
<i>He was perfect,</i>
<i>and this is a mess.</i>

144
00:08:07,125 --> 00:08:08,083
<i>What the hell happened to him?</i>

145
00:08:08,166 --> 00:08:11,208
<i>Where's the prodigy</i>
<i>I looked up to?</i>

146
00:08:11,291 --> 00:08:15,250
<i>Two whole years of my life,</i>

147
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:17,125
<i>I waited for this?</i>

148
00:08:29,375 --> 00:08:29,958
- [playing stops]
- [gasps]

149
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:32,000
[gasps]

150
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:37,625
Enough.

151
00:08:37,708 --> 00:08:40,416
Stop messing with my head,
already.

152
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:49,291
- Would you look at that?

153
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:55,708
He just stopped.

154
00:09:03,291 --> 00:09:06,125
[audience murmuring]

155
00:09:10,041 --> 00:09:11,000
- What's happening?

156
00:09:11,083 --> 00:09:13,416
- Huh. I guess
he's a normal kid after all.

157
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:14,958
- Think he got stage fright
or what?

158
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,375
- Disqualified.

159
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:18,333
They won't even score him.

160
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:21,375
- [scoffs]<i> Couldn't hack it.</i>

161
00:09:23,333 --> 00:09:25,000
- If you cut your song short,

162
00:09:25,083 --> 00:09:26,375
no matter what the reason is,

163
00:09:26,458 --> 00:09:28,583
you're out of the competition.

164
00:09:28,666 --> 00:09:30,625
[murmuring continues]

165
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:33,125
[Kousei sighs]

166
00:09:33,208 --> 00:09:35,041
<i>Here we go again.</i>

167
00:09:39,666 --> 00:09:41,166
<i>Tried to play.</i>

168
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:42,250
<i>Lost my notes.</i>

169
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:44,666
<i>Got disqualified.</i>

170
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:47,125
<i>Both of us.</i>

171
00:09:47,208 --> 00:09:49,958
<i>You only stopped</i>
<i>because I did.</i>

172
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:50,708
<i>You would have been</i>
<i>fine without me.</i>

173
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:53,541
<i>Tell me,</i>

174
00:09:53,625 --> 00:09:55,708
<i>what were you playing for</i>
<i>after that?</i>

175
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,875
[sighs]

176
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:04,458
<i>You're a tyrant. You know that?</i>

177
00:10:04,541 --> 00:10:07,250
<i>Always barging in</i>
<i>on my thoughts.</i>

178
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:17,000
♪♪

179
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:18,583
<i>Even the you</i>
<i>that's in my head...</i>

180
00:10:22,500 --> 00:10:24,875
<i>...you refuse to let me</i>
<i>throw in the towel.</i>

181
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:31,875
<i>When you started again,</i>

182
00:10:31,958 --> 00:10:34,416
<i>what inspired you</i>
<i>to keep on playing?</i>

183
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:39,125
[heart beating]

184
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:49,625
[beating continues]

185
00:10:56,458 --> 00:10:59,041
Kousei and Kaori:<i> Again!</i>

186
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:00,916
[Playing
"Etude Opus 25, Number 5"]

187
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,958
<i>- He's playing?</i>
<i>- It's no good.</i>

188
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:07,250
<i>He's jumping all over the place</i>
<i>with his tempo.</i>

189
00:11:09,375 --> 00:11:09,791
Kaori:<i> Picture it in your head.</i>

190
00:11:12,166 --> 00:11:13,500
<i>How do you wanna</i>
<i>play this piece,</i>

191
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:16,458
<i>and who are you playing it for?</i>

192
00:11:16,541 --> 00:11:19,041
Kousei:<i> When you began again,</i>

193
00:11:19,125 --> 00:11:21,291
<i>why'd you do it?</i>

194
00:11:21,375 --> 00:11:23,333
<i>What was your inspiration?</i>

195
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,416
-<i> I know all of that,</i>

196
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:27,250
<i>and I want you anyway.</i>

197
00:11:27,333 --> 00:11:30,083
<i>- I play the notes,</i>
<i>but I can't hear them.</i>

198
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:32,916
["Etude Opus 25, Number 5"
continues]

199
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,791
<i>- I give the accompanist job</i>
<i>to Friend A.</i>

200
00:11:38,375 --> 00:11:41,666
-<i> Yeah, you did.</i>

201
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:45,041
- [wind blowing]
- [birds chirping]

202
00:11:59,083 --> 00:12:01,791
<i>So I-I'm gonna play for you.</i>

203
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:08,750
["Etude Opus 25, Number 5"
continues]

204
00:12:10,458 --> 00:12:13,166
- [gasps]
- [gasps]

205
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:15,750
-<i> I can't get a bead</i>
<i>on this kid.</i>

206
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,541
<i>At the top of the piece,</i>

207
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:18,291
<i>he played like a robot,</i>

208
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:21,125
<i>so sterile and precise,</i>

209
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:24,041
<i>then he thrashed around</i>
<i>like a lost child</i>

210
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:25,125
<i>desperate for a familiar face,</i>

211
00:12:25,208 --> 00:12:27,833
<i>and now he's</i>
<i>something else entirely.</i>

212
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,291
-<i> He stops,</i>

213
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:33,041
<i>and then he gives us this?</i>

214
00:12:33,125 --> 00:12:34,208
<i>I can't believe</i>
<i>it's the same guy.</i>

215
00:12:34,291 --> 00:12:36,833
<i>It's like there's</i>
<i>three different versions</i>

216
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:38,041
<i>of him in there.</i>

217
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:43,333
<i>- It's not just</i>
<i>his playing that's changed.</i>

218
00:12:43,416 --> 00:12:44,958
<i>It's his sound, too.</i>

219
00:12:47,625 --> 00:12:48,625
<i>The notes...</i>

220
00:12:48,708 --> 00:12:49,791
<i>they're sparkling.</i>

221
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:57,458
<i>- I stopped</i>
<i>in the middle of my song.</i>

222
00:12:57,541 --> 00:13:00,416
<i>I'm disqualified,</i>

223
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,583
<i>just like</i>
<i>a certain tyrant I can name.</i>

224
00:13:02,666 --> 00:13:02,791
- [growls]

225
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:06,541
<i>It means that you're</i>
<i>gonna shine</i>

226
00:13:06,625 --> 00:13:09,041
<i>like a star up there.</i>

227
00:13:09,125 --> 00:13:09,833
<i>Give the performance</i>
<i>of your life</i>

228
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:12,041
<i>with everything you've got.</i>

229
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:15,208
<i>No one can tell you how.</i>

230
00:13:15,291 --> 00:13:17,208
<i>It's your decision to make.</i>

231
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:20,666
<i>Guess that means</i>
<i>you're not Chopin after all.</i>

232
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:24,291
<i>You're you, no matter what.</i>

233
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:32,708
<i>- They light the darkness</i>
<i>like shooting stars.</i>

234
00:13:34,166 --> 00:13:35,583
<i>I'd look at the night alone,</i>

235
00:13:35,666 --> 00:13:36,791
<i>afraid that it would devour me.</i>

236
00:13:39,416 --> 00:13:40,916
<i>With Watari,</i>
<i>it had no rhyme or reason.</i>

237
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:45,083
<i>And when it was me and Tsubaki,</i>

238
00:13:45,166 --> 00:13:47,208
<i>it was so incredibly bright,</i>

239
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:47,833
<i>but seemed fragile.</i>

240
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:57,583
<i>How is the sky going to look</i>
<i>with you?</i>

241
00:13:57,666 --> 00:14:04,291
♪♪

242
00:14:04,375 --> 00:14:11,958
♪♪

243
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:15,500
Emi:<i> The dry smell</i>
<i>of chalk dust.</i>

244
00:14:15,583 --> 00:14:18,625
<i>A broken window hastily fixed.</i>

245
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:20,750
<i>The sound of distant cheering.</i>

246
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:23,750
<i>The shadows</i>
<i>of cherry blossom petals.</i>

247
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:26,666
<i>The breath of one asleep.</i>

248
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,291
<i>The concert hall is gone...</i>

249
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:34,250
<i>...vanished by Arima's hand.</i>

250
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:36,333
["Etude Opus 25, Number 5"
continues]

251
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:41,541
<i>All of us are drifting</i>
<i>into his world.</i>

252
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:55,916
[Kaori murmurs]

253
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:58,666
[violin playing]

254
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:01,791
Kaori:<i> Maybe we bomb out there.</i>

255
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:04,583
<i>Maybe we step</i>
<i>off that stage in defeat,</i>

256
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,625
<i>but we are gonna play.</i>

257
00:15:06,708 --> 00:15:08,750
<i>If there's a crowd</i>
<i>and a chance to play,</i>

258
00:15:08,833 --> 00:15:10,166
<i>I'm taking it.</i>

259
00:15:14,666 --> 00:15:16,625
-<i> This, this is who I am!</i>

260
00:15:16,708 --> 00:15:20,375
-<i> Let it ring! Let it ring!</i>

261
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:22,708
Kaori:<i> And the people</i>
<i>who hear it,</i>

262
00:15:22,791 --> 00:15:24,583
<i>they'll never forget me.</i>

263
00:15:24,666 --> 00:15:28,625
<i>Part of me will echo</i>
<i>in their hearts forever.</i>

264
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:34,333
-<i> I play for you</i>
<i>and you alone.</i>

265
00:15:34,416 --> 00:15:40,875
♪♪

266
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:42,416
<i>You're all that matters.</i>

267
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:47,333
<i>Thank you for everything,</i>

268
00:15:47,416 --> 00:15:48,333
<i>every note,</i>

269
00:15:48,416 --> 00:15:50,791
<i>every glance...</i>

270
00:15:54,250 --> 00:15:55,875
<i>...every you.</i>

271
00:15:55,958 --> 00:15:57,333
[piano and violin continue]

272
00:15:57,416 --> 00:16:04,541
♪♪

273
00:16:04,625 --> 00:16:07,541
-<i> Is this the same Arima?</i>

274
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:08,458
- [sniffling]

275
00:16:08,541 --> 00:16:09,958
<i>It's so pretty,</i>

276
00:16:10,041 --> 00:16:13,750
<i>so how come I feel</i>
<i>like I wanna cry?</i>

277
00:16:14,791 --> 00:16:17,666
-<i> Age must be making me soft.</i>

278
00:16:18,458 --> 00:16:20,583
<i>Hearing such honest emotion,</i>

279
00:16:20,666 --> 00:16:22,083
<i>it hurts my heart a little.</i>

280
00:16:24,666 --> 00:16:26,375
-<i> Return to us.</i>

281
00:16:26,458 --> 00:16:28,375
<i>Return to us.</i>

282
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:30,416
<i>Arima!</i>

283
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:32,791
Kousei:<i> I hear</i>
<i>her soft breathing</i>

284
00:16:32,875 --> 00:16:36,625
<i>as she sleeps, like a cat.</i>

285
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,750
<i>A single petal</i>
<i>that drifted into my life</i>

286
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:44,916
<i>and hit me with a melodica.</i>

287
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,875
<i>The girl who likes</i>
<i>my best friend.</i>

288
00:16:50,125 --> 00:16:51,583
<i>These images...</i>

289
00:16:51,666 --> 00:16:53,625
<i>will they reach her?</i>

290
00:16:53,708 --> 00:16:55,916
[piano and violin continue]

291
00:16:56,000 --> 00:17:02,458
♪♪

292
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:10,750
♪♪

293
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:13,916
- Welcome home, Kousei Arima.

294
00:17:17,666 --> 00:17:19,000
-<i> You're here within my heart.</i>

295
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:22,500
<i>I can feel you.</i>

296
00:17:26,583 --> 00:17:29,000
- Two years later,

297
00:17:29,083 --> 00:17:30,958
you've finally woken up.

298
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:36,416
Cat:<i> That girl</i>
<i>told you true, Kousei.</i>

299
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,458
<i>Freedom is what you find</i>
<i>out there.</i>

300
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:48,333
♪♪

301
00:17:48,416 --> 00:17:50,666
<i>Look at you, free as a bird.</i>

302
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,291
- [gasps]

303
00:17:55,375 --> 00:18:01,916
♪♪

304
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:08,500
♪♪

305
00:18:08,583 --> 00:18:15,333
♪♪

306
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:21,875
♪♪

307
00:18:21,958 --> 00:18:28,500
♪♪

308
00:18:28,583 --> 00:18:29,791
[piece ends]

309
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:38,000
[footsteps echoing]

310
00:18:50,791 --> 00:18:52,500
- Huh?
- [gasps]

311
00:18:52,583 --> 00:18:54,500
- It's over?

312
00:18:54,583 --> 00:18:56,625
- Oh, right. Time to applaud.

313
00:18:56,708 --> 00:18:59,416
- [applause]
- What just happened?

314
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:02,208
- I feel like I don't even know.

315
00:19:02,291 --> 00:19:11,083
♪♪

316
00:19:11,166 --> 00:19:13,875
<i>- Of course Takeshi's</i>
<i>thrown off by that.</i>

317
00:19:13,958 --> 00:19:16,583
<i>Truth be told,</i>
<i>he's not the only one.</i>

318
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:20,041
[heart beating]

319
00:19:21,708 --> 00:19:23,541
<i>It still resonates?</i>

320
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:25,750
<i>Is he getting better,</i>

321
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:28,583
<i>or was this just a fluke?</i>

322
00:19:30,208 --> 00:19:31,958
<i>Look at him,</i>

323
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:35,291
<i>standing there without even</i>
<i>the slightest twinge of</i>
<i>regret.</i>

324
00:19:39,125 --> 00:19:41,125
Kousei:
<i>There's scattered applause,</i>

325
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:42,750
<i>not that it matters.</i>

326
00:19:44,166 --> 00:19:47,958
<i>I played for the sake</i>
<i>of one person.</i>

327
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:51,458
<i>Did it reach her?</i>

328
00:19:55,625 --> 00:19:56,875
<i>I hope that it did.</i>

329
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:03,958
[sighs]

330
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:11,458
♪♪

331
00:20:11,541 --> 00:20:12,250
[gasps]

332
00:20:15,708 --> 00:20:17,833
["Kirameki" playing]

333
00:20:23,166 --> 00:20:24,625
[singing in Japanese]

334
00:20:24,708 --> 00:20:35,000
♪♪

335
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:43,750
♪♪

336
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:54,166
♪♪

337
00:20:54,250 --> 00:21:03,625
♪♪

338
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:13,333
♪♪

339
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:22,708
♪♪

340
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:32,375
♪♪

341
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:41,875
♪♪

342
00:21:41,958 --> 00:21:51,416
♪♪

343
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:54,416
- That was outrageous,
a damn travesty!

344
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:56,208
Could he have been
any less prepared...

345
00:21:56,291 --> 00:21:57,750
- Please, sir! Quiet down!
-...for today's competition?!

346
00:21:57,833 --> 00:21:59,875
This is meant to be a moment
for serious musicians!

347
00:21:59,958 --> 00:22:01,291
Emi:<i> He's right to be angry.</i>

348
00:22:01,375 --> 00:22:03,208
<i>Arima wasn't up to par.</i>

349
00:22:03,291 --> 00:22:03,875
<i>If he prepped for this,</i>
<i>I couldn't tell.</i>

350
00:22:03,958 --> 00:22:06,666
-...a rank amateur!

351
00:22:06,750 --> 00:22:08,416
Emi:<i> Still...</i>

352
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,666
<i>those notes of his,</i>

353
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:11,416
<i>they felt like April.</i>

354
00:22:14,291 --> 00:22:16,041
- He's an interesting boy.

355
00:22:16,125 --> 00:22:17,500
- [gasps]

356
00:22:17,583 --> 00:22:17,916
- I trust you'd agree.

357
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,708
[chuckles]

358
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:22,708
- [chuckles]

359
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:26,375
Ochiai:<i> The puppet</i>
<i>cut his strings.</i>

360
00:22:26,458 --> 00:22:29,166
<i>I wonder where his legs</i>
<i>will take him.</i>

361
00:22:29,250 --> 00:22:30,416
<i>It was rough,</i>

362
00:22:30,500 --> 00:22:33,375
<i>but if he gives himself</i>
<i>a chance,</i>

363
00:22:33,458 --> 00:22:35,833
<i>he may master</i>
<i>those emotions yet.</i>

364
00:22:38,958 --> 00:22:41,083
- I wonder what changed for him.

365
00:22:41,166 --> 00:22:43,083
- Yeah. That kid kicked ass.

366
00:22:43,166 --> 00:22:43,333
- Huh?
- Hmm?

367
00:22:46,958 --> 00:22:49,875
- Uh-huh. Pretty good.

368
00:22:49,958 --> 00:22:52,416
For a quitter.

